  "why": "The paper provides diagnostic analysis of discovered failures by characterizing their properties and relating them to model-internal signals (neuron activation patterns). The authors show that crash-triggering state sequences produce distinct neuron activation patterns (t-SNE visualization, clustering) and build an abnormal-behavior detector from these internal signals; they also use the findings to guide repairs (fine-tuning) that reduce crashes. However, the paper does not trace failures to deeper root causes such as biased/corrupted training data, spurious input features, or overfitting, nor does it link failures to specific dataset or training-process vulnerabilities. Therefore the diagnostic insight is substantial but partial, matching the \"Medium\" category.",
